SIMPLE: hoof
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hoof
<hw>Hoof</hw> <pr>(h⟦oomac⟧f)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Hoofs</plw> <pr>(h⟦oomac⟧fs)</pr>, very rarely <plw>Hooves</plw>
<pr>(h⟦oomac⟧vz)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[OE. <ets>hof</ets>, AS.
<ets>h⟦omac⟧f</ets>; akin to D. <ets>hoef</ets>, G. <ets>huf</ets>, OHG.
<ets>huof</ets>, Icel. <ets>h⟦omac⟧fr</ets>, Sw. <ets>hof</ets>, Dan.
<ets>hov</ets>; cf. Russ. <ets>kopuito</ets>, Skr.
<ets>⟦cced⟧apha</ets>. ⟦root⟧225.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The horny
substance or case that covers or terminates the feet of certain animals,
as horses, oxen, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>On burnished <qex>hooves</qex> his war horse trode.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A hoofed animal; a beast.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Our cattle also shall go with us; there shall not a
<qex>hoof</qex> be left behind.</q> <rj><qau>Ex. x. 26.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Geom.)</fld> <def>See <er>Ungula</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hoof</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Hoof
<hw>Hoof</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To walk as
cattle.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>William Scott.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To be on a tramp; to foot.</def> <mark>[Slang,
U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To hoof it</b></col>, <cd>to foot it.</cd> -- <col><b>On
the hoof</b></col>, <cd>of cattle, standing (on the hoof); not
slaughtered.</cd> -- <col><b>beef on the hoof</b></col>, <cd>live
cattle.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hoofbound</ent>⟦br⟧
